Target: `module/LLMWorkflow/retrieval/IncidentBundle.ps1`

Reason:
- surface meaningful cleanup failures in atomic bundle export
- add fallback visibility where run ID resolution silently collapses to `unknown`
- avoid vague parse-failure diagnostics during incident searches

---

## Patch A: surface temp-file cleanup failure in `Export-IncidentBundle`

Current code:

```powershell
catch {
    # Clean up temp file on failure
    if (Test-Path -LiteralPath $tempPath) {
        Remove-Item -LiteralPath $tempPath -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
    }

    return @{
        Success = $false
        Path = $OutputPath
        IncidentId = $Incident.incidentId
        BytesWritten = 0
        Error = $_.Exception.Message
    }
}
```

Replace with:

```powershell
catch {
    # Clean up temp file on failure
    if ($tempPath -and (Test-Path -LiteralPath $tempPath)) {
        try {
            Remove-Item -LiteralPath $tempPath -Force -ErrorAction Stop
        }
        catch {
            Write-Warning "[IncidentBundle] Failed to remove temporary incident bundle '$tempPath' after export failure: $($_.Exception.Message)"
        }
    }

    return @{
        Success = $false
        Path = $OutputPath
        IncidentId = $Incident.incidentId
        BytesWritten = 0
        Error = $_.Exception.Message
    }
}
```

## Patch B: add fallback visibility in `New-AnswerIncidentBundle`

Current code:

```powershell
try {
    $runIdCmd = Get-Command Get-CurrentRunId -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
    if ($runIdCmd) {
        $RunId = & $runIdCmd -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
    }
}
catch {
    $RunId = "unknown"
}
if ([string]::IsNullOrEmpty($RunId)) {
    $RunId = "unknown"
}
```

Replace with:

```powershell
try {
    $runIdCmd = Get-Command Get-CurrentRunId -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
    if ($runIdCmd) {
        $RunId = & $runIdCmd -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
    }
}
catch {
    Write-Verbose "[IncidentBundle] Get-CurrentRunId failed, using fallback run ID: $($_.Exception.Message)"
    $RunId = "unknown"
}
if ([string]::IsNullOrEmpty($RunId)) {
    Write-Verbose "[IncidentBundle] Run ID was empty, using fallback value 'unknown'"
    $RunId = "unknown"
}
```

## Patch C: tighten search parse diagnostics in `Search-IncidentBundles`

Current code:

```powershell
catch {
    Write-Verbose "[IncidentBundle] Failed to parse $($file.Name): $_"
}
```

Replace with:

```powershell
catch {
    Write-Verbose "[IncidentBundle] Failed to parse incident file '$($file.Name)': $($_.Exception.Message)"
}
```
